ent-RMCHeadCapWestonYamadaDark-name = Weston-Yamada cap
ent-RMCHeadCapWestonYamadaDark-desc = A dark cap enscribed with the Weston-Yamada 'Wings' logo, representing corporate justice.

ent-RMCHeadCapManager-name = manager's hat
ent-RMCHeadCapManager-desc = Belongs to someone very important. Has minor protection to all damage types.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCDirector-name = director's hat
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCDirector-desc = Belongs to someone very important. Has minor protection to all damage types.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCEngineer-name = pmc engineer helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCEngineer-desc = An advanced technician helmet with a black finish, including advanced welding protection and resistance to the potential industrial hazards, but has less kevlar against potential firefights.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCKutjevoMedical-name = We-Ya corporate medic helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCKutjevoMedical-desc = A basic skull-helm worn by corporate security assets. This variant comes with a wider brim to protect the user from the harsh climate of the desert and has a medical cross across the front.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCKutjevoSecurity-name = We-Ya corporate security helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCKutjevoSecurity-desc = A basic skull-helm worn by corporate security assets. This variant comes with a wider brim to protect the user from the harsh climate of the desert.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCKutjevo-name = kutjevo helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCKutjevo-desc = Standard issued helmet for the workers of Kutjevo. Contains a small webbing to hold small items like pens, oil or even a photo of a loved one.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCRiot-name = RC6 helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCRiot-desc = The standard UN Riot Control 6 helmet is of odd design, lacking a face shield by default (mounting points are available). The distinct white pattern and red emblem are synonymous with oppression throughout the rim.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCCorporate-name = We-Ya corporate security helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCCorporate-desc = A basic skull-helm worn by corporate security assets, graded to protect your head from an unruly scientist armed with a crowbar.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCCommando-name = шлем ЧВК M5X

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCGunner-name = PMC specialist operator helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCGunner-desc = A modification of the standard PMC tactical helmet, featuring a frontal shield to protect the user's from shrapnel and small arms fire while operating heavy weaponry.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCOfficer-name = PMC beret
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCOfficer-desc = The pinnacle of fashion for any aspiring mercenary leader. Designed to protect the head from light impacts.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCTactical-name = tactical helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCTactical-desc = A contender for service with the Royal Crown Marines, it is presently, exclusively, field tested by Weston-Yamada mercenaries. Features a ballistic mask and integrated display connected to the visor.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMC-name = PMC tactical cap
ent-ArmorHelmetPMC-desc = A protective cap made from flexible kevlar. Standard issue for most security forms in the place of a helmet.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCBlack-name = PMC black tactical cap
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCBlack-desc = A protective cap made from flexible kevlar. Standard issue for most security forms in the place of a helmet.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCFieldOfficer-name = PMC field officer beret
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCFieldOfficer-desc = The pinnacle of fashion for any aspiring mercenary leader. Designed to protect the head from light impacts.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCommando-name = We-Ya commando helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCommando-desc = A standard enclosed helmet utilized by Weston-Yamada Commandos.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCommandoDamaged-name = damaged We-Ya Commando helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCommandoDamaged-desc = A standard enclosed helmet utilized by Weston-Yamada Commandos. Has been through a lot of wear and tear.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCDeathsquad-name = PMC M5X helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCDeathsquad-desc = A fully enclosed, armored helmet made to complete the M5X exoskeleton armor.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCDeathsquadAlt-name = PMC M5X helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCDeathsquadAlt-desc = A fully enclosed, armored helmet made to complete the M5X exoskeleton armor. This one has had a skull scratched into the visor.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCDark-name = We-Ya armored cap
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCDark-desc = A protective cap made from flexible kevlar. Standard issue for most security forms in the place of a helmet.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCCorporateLead-name = We-Ya corporate security helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCCorporateLead-desc = A basic skull-helm worn by corporate security assets. This variant is worn by low-level guards that have too much brainmatter to fit into the old one. Or so they say.

ent-ArmorHelmetPMCRiotShield-name = RC6 helmet
ent-ArmorHelmetPMCRiotShield-desc = The standard UN Riot Control 6 helmet is of odd design, lacking a face shield by default (mounting points are available). The distinct white pattern and red emblem are synonymous with oppression throughout the rim.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCorporateHybrisa-name = We-Ya corporate security helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCorporateHybrisa-desc = A basic skull-helm with a orange safety visor fitted. Worn by corporate security assets, graded to protect your head from an unruly scientist armed with a crowbar.

ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCorporateLeadHybrisa-name = We-Ya corporate security helmet
ent-RMCArmorHelmetPMCCorporateLeadHybrisa-desc = A basic skull-helm with a orange safety visor fitted. Worn by corporate security assets. This variant is worn by low-level guards that have too much brainmatter to fit into the old one. Or so they say.

ent-RMCHeadBeretWeYa-name = Weston-Yamada beret
ent-RMCHeadBeretWeYa-desc = Show off your megacorp pride with this stylish beret!

